\v 6 M…ôr…®g nar k…®rikian…ô …ôm…ô e nakasor rhuv…ô: Naks…ôm…ôk…®n norien has m…®n…ô kape nukwao kape Nikolas\f + \fr 2:6 \ft  Nikolas in yhajoun eiku…ô k…®rik. Tukm…ô ror in ramhajoun m…ô narp…®nien r…®rk…ôk tuk t…ôvhag…ô has; m…®m…ô ‚ÄúP…ôh k…®sor …ôm…ô t…ôvhag…ô has mamharp…®n.‚Äù\f*, r…ômhen …ôm…ô k…®n yame yo yak…ôm…ôk…®n …ôri…ô.   
\pi1
\v 7 Yermam…ô yame n…®m…ôt…®rg…®n rar…ô, tukram…ôkeikei m…ôr…®g huv…ô n…ôgkiarien yame Nanm…®n kape Kughen ramni-p…ôn tuk nim…ôhuak m…®n…ô. Yermam…ô yame rapita ye narowag…®nien e, Yo jakeighaan k…®n in m…ô tukr…ôn kw…ônkwai nai yame rav…ôhsi-p…ôn n…®mraghien, yame rauru…ô ye n…ôsimien kape Kughen.‚Äù\x - \xo 2:7 \xt Jen 2:9; 3:22-24; Rom 5:12,18; 6:23; Rev 22:2\x*   
